text: Malyye Shidy () is a rural locality (a village) in Bashshidinsky Selsoviet, Nurimanovsky District, Bashkortostan, Russia. The population was 202 as of 2010. There are 2 streets. == Geography == It is located 4 km from Krasnaya Gorka, 55 km from Baygildino. == References == Category:Rural localities in Nurimanovsky District
title: Malyye Shidy
